    <description>
LightCrosshair is a lightweight, high-performance crosshair overlay for competitive gaming on Windows 10/11.

## Features
- Custom crosshair builder with full shape control
- Lightweight performance overlay modes with ultra-lightweight mode
- Frame Cap Assistant with no active real limiter backend
- Process-aware display color management (per-profile gamma/contrast/brightness)
- Modern profile workflow with immutable defaults
- Low CPU footprint optimized for gameplay
- Multi-monitor support with DPI awareness
- Screen recording detection for streaming/recording

## Requirements
- Windows 10 or later
- .NET 8.0 Windows Desktop Runtime (required for the current framework-dependent package)

## Installation
This package downloads the official LightCrosshair 1.7.0 installer from the GitHub Release and verifies its SHA256 checksum before installation.

After installation, launch LightCrosshair from your Start Menu.
    </description>
    <summary>Lightweight gaming crosshair overlay with FPS counter and color management</summary>
    <releaseNotes>
v1.7.0 (May 2026): Adds NVIDIA per-app FPS cap profile binding fixes, profile audit information, Low Latency and VSync controls, read-only G-SYNC and Low Latency CPL state display, NVIDIA helper process isolation, GPU Driver tab polish, primary-display Frame Cap Assistant defaults, and continued safe asInvoker operation.

See https://github.com/PrimeBuild-pc/LightCrosshair/releases for full details.
    </releaseNotes>
